social_posts.post_text: An officer with The Miami Dade Police Department’s Robbery Intervention Detail was involved in a ambush style shooting this afternoon. The 34 year old officer has an injury to his face, doctors were looking at a fragment lodged in his cheek. He will recover. In 2022 the MDPD lost one officer, 3 have been shot, 2 stabbed. The MDPD Director says the department hasn’t seen violence at this level for about 11 years. One person has been detained in relation to this. More on local10.com

Car theft is a popular choice for criminals today after seeing a decline of the crime in the 1990’s. 

According to the National Insurance Crime Bureau, for the first time since 2008 vehicle thefts surpassed 1 Million nationwide. Florida ranks top five in the country for thefts with close to 46,000 in 2022. 
Full story on Local10.com

Today I spoke with a brave 6 year old girl who fought off a man attempting to kidnap her. She was playing outside when he grabbed her, she bit him and he let her go before running off. Miami police arrested the guy, he’s facing kidnapping and child abuse charges. 6 year old Lyric credits her mother with teaching her to fight back and not talk to strangers. When I asked her if she was scared she replied “No.” 💪🏽
